options.text: This powerful ingredient has a high volume of inulin fiber, which can help boost several aspects of the digestive system. Acting as an efficacious prebiotic, inulin can encourage the production of good bacteria within the gut, helping to support your pup’s digestive system.

Found in the intestine, Bacillus coagulans (B. coagulans) is a bacteria known for supporting and aiding a dog's immune system. This probiotic is a beneficial microorganism that can maintain the immune system and response, supporting occasional discomforts.

Full of antioxidants, nutrients, and probiotics, honey is a wonderful and powerful ingredient in our probiotic chews. This sweet addition can help provide your pet with bacterial balancing properties and a normal inflammatory response that can help support digestive tract health.

Pumpkin produces beneficial fatty acids that stimulate intestinal sodium. Plus, this colorful fruit contains a soluble fiber that can help optimize stool consistency by absorbing water, supporting healthy bowel movements and digestion.

A Proprietary Blend of (Bacillus coagulans, Lactobacillus reuteri, Bifidobacterium bifidum, Bifidobacterium longum, Lactobacillus brevis, Lactobacillus casei, Lactobacillus plantarum, Streptococcus thermophilus), Pumpkin (Cucurbita pepo), Honey, Inulin (Agave), FOS - Fructooligosaccharides (Saccharum officinarum), Ascorbic Acid, Cane Molasses, Coconut Glycerin, Dried Brewer’s Yeast, Dried Whey, Lecithin, Liquid Smoke Flavor, Mixed Tocopherols, Pork Gelatin, Salmon oil, Spray Dried Pork Liver, Tapioca Starch.

options.quote: He’s been on these probiotics for 2 months now and we’ve seen absolutely dramatic changes. He seems to be enjoying life a whole lot more
The probiotic chews from PetLab Co. are just what I was looking for & you can see the significant change

questions.question: At what age can my pup start using Probiotic chews?
questions.answer: The probiotic soft chews are suitable for dogs of any age and breed, however, we recommend introducing this treat to your pup slowly when they are around 6 months old. If you have any concerns please consult your vet.

questions.question: How many Probiotic chews come in a tub?
What flavor are PetLab Co.’s Probiotic chews?
questions.answer: Each of our tasty Probiotic chews are pork flavored - which will leave your pup begging for more!

questions.question: What happens if I accidentally give my dog too many Probiotic chews?
questions.answer: If you accidentally give your dog too many chews, see a veterinarian as soon as possible. If you’re unsure how many chews to give your dog, please see the Directions for use at the top of the page.

questions.question: Are the Probiotic chews safe for a dog with Kidney Disease?
questions.answer: We try to keep our products as natural as we possibly can, using ingredients of the highest quality in our soft chew to ensure your pup reacts effectively and safely. Please consult with your vet first if you have any concerns.

questions.question: Is this product safe for humans?
questions.answer: All our products are intended to be consumed by our furry friends and are not safe for human consumption. Please keep packages out of reach of children.

questions.question: Are Probiotic chews safe for cats?
questions.answer: Our chews are safe if your cat ingests them, however, we would not recommend you make it a part of their complementary feed.
